				<div class="col-md-6">
					<div class="wrapper">
						<strong>Some things that require a Spanish bank account:</strong>
						<ul>
							<li>If you want to get a telephone line and internet.</li>
							<li>If you want a contract from a mobile.</li>
							<li>Pay electricity and water bills.</li>
							<li>Pay car/bike insurance.</li>
							<li>Receiving a salary if you are an employee.</li>
							<li>Paying Social Security fees if you are self-employed.</li>
							<li>Accountants fees to your Spanish Company Account.</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<br>
			And lastly, most banks have international employees who speak English and some other European languages and all banks have got Internet Banking facilities in more than multiple languages.
			</p>
